"L7130 7.94"
Is that value on charger only???

Post exact voltage for PPBUS_G3H and 3V42 with only charger connected.
BTW, use original Magsafe 2 charger.

Also need PM_BATLOW_L, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PM_RSMRST_L, PM_PWRBTN_L, PM_SLP_SUS_L.

title: 820-00164-A no booting - no water damage - no image - no fanspin - light on magsafe
message:
Stop to check coil voltage on both pins.
You can find the DC voltage on its output pin connected to filter capacitor.

Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for drop pulse ( 3-0-3V) at PM_PWRBTN_L at same time.
If present, then check if all PM_SLP_Sx_L signals pulse at the same moment.

title: 820-00164-A no booting - no water damage - no image - no fanspin - light on magsafe
message:
SMC_ONOFF_L  drop pulse 0.4-3.39V
PM_PWRBTN_L  drop pulse 0.4-3.3V
PM_SLP_S0_L on smc trigger getting different V pulse between 0.4-1.4V
PM_SLP_S3_L on smc trigger getting different V pulse between 0.2-0.8V
PM_SLP_S4_L on smc trigger getting different V pulse between 0.4-1.4V
PM_SLP_S5_L on smc trigger getting different V pulse between 0.4-1.4V

title: 820-00164-A no booting - no water damage - no image - no fanspin - light on magsafe
message:
In this case you should have pulse at all big coils; check that.
Also check ALL_SYS_PWRGD.
Inspect U1950 area.

title: 820-00164-A no booting - no water damage - no image - no fanspin - light on magsafe
message:
yes we have pulse on all big coils
also pulse on ALL_SYS_PWRGD
U1950 area looks good. 
Any more ideas? Or we hit a deadend?

title: 820-00164-A no booting - no water damage - no image - no fanspin - light on magsafe
message:
Check all power rails from pages 55/56.

Also check voltage on all L/C blocks near CPU, close to edge board; both sides of each coil.
